social_posts.post_text:
Pick your early morning mediation on Nielson Beach. Whether it's out on the waves, walking the mandala, watching the sunrise from the sand or reflecting on the coffee and good company at @the_beach_mill. 

Now set for a chill and productive week. It's only 2 weeks till Christmas, how are you keeping it cruisy?

#optoutsideeveryday #getoutside #nielsonbeach #woongarracoast #thegreatoutdoors #mandalameditation #beachmandala #happiestoutside #beachvibes #coastalliving #findmeoutside #coralcoast #visitbundaberg #sealovers #thisisqueensland #bargara

A bit of a wet day in Auckland for a trip out to our old home town of Browns Bay. 

The rain was driving down the beach ruling out much of a walk but the 21 Days Cafe was a happy new discovery for brunch. Delicious food, great location and a fab team.

#21daysbarandbrasserie #brownsbaycafe #brownsbay #loveauckland #visitauckland🇳🇿

An early Sunday morning coffee at The Beach Mill on Neilson Beach is hard to beat but I have to wonder if the Chureito Pagoda on my coffee cup is the universe telling me that it’s been too long, it’s time to get back to Japan.

Still looking a lot like summer here. A bit of morning practice in my TN, listening to the waves and enjoying a Flat White done right by the ladies  at @somewheretoeat_cafe . Welcoming back the coffee van to Kelly’s / Archie’s Beach!

#somewheretoeat #coffeeaddict #coffeetravel #visitbargara #visitbundaberg #bargarabeach #archiesbeach #kellysbeach #beachvibes #sunshinetherapy #travelersnotebook #travelerscompany

One of the best parts of staying at Mooloolaba Beach is walking this stretching of sand at sunrise. It’s the quietest it will be all day but still plenty of activity between the surf life savers, serious swimmers, walkers, runners and surfers. Definitely one of my happy places.

You can pick up a dawn coffee under the surf lifesaving club if you need a little boost to get you going.

#mooloolaba #mooloolababeach #visitsunshinecoast #beachvibes #beachdayeveryday #discoverqueensland #sunrisesky #oceanlove #thisisqueensland #visitqld

I do love the walkway from Bargara to Mon Repos but this track along grassy paths, over salt pans and along the beach is my favourite. 

We are past turtle nesting and hatching season now and this week a few early humpback whales have made their way up past this part of the coast on their annual winter migration in easy spotting distance of the shoreline.  Soon they will be followed by ~40,000 of their nearest and dearest on their way to northern Queenslands tropical waters for breeding season. I can’t wait!

#bargarabeach #monreposconservationpark #widebayburnett #visitbundaberg #beachwalks #thisisqueensland #winterinqueensland #bargara #monreposbeach #lovequeensland #beachlife

Just one of many fabulous ocean pools along the Bundaberg coastline between Elliott Heads and Bargara. This one is off the Turtle walkway at Innes Park. 

With the temperature today not going over 25 ° c, I’ll sip my coffee from here and watch the wildlife rather than taking a dip but it’s a gorgeous spot all year round and another fabulous ‘shorts and tee shirt’ winter day in the Wide Bay.

#innespark #visitbundaberg #thisisqueensland #coralcoastqld #beachwalks #aussieroadtrip #lovethereef #exploreaustralia👣 #exploreaustralia #whalehighway #oceanpools #bargaraheadlands

Had a couple of hours to get some errands ticked off in town ….yeah-nah… that would mean walking past @indulge_80 , one of my fave cafes and that would just be rude.

#visitbundaberg #tastebundaberg #indulgecafe #coffeetime #coffeelovers #streetart #discoverqueensland #lovebundy

Got to love a walk and sunrise coffee at @the_beach_mill while watching the humpback whales putting on a show out front.

#visitbargara #visitbundaberg #bargara #neilsonsbeach #whalewatching #beachlife🌴

After 3 rainy days we were clawing at the door to get outside this morning.  Nothing too energetic, just chilling on the beach, sand beneath our feet, exploring the rock pools, drinking coffee and listening to this weeks playlist on my new Sudio N2 Pro earbuds. 

We’ve both lived and travelled with @sudio headphones and earbuds for many years now and these N2 Pro are the best yet. 

They have great sound, are really comfortable, and are IPX4 so they are sweat and splash proof 💦, all the essential ticks for an Aussie summer.  They also have active noise cancelling which I can’t wait to test out on our next flight.

If you have had your eye on a new pair for summer or a gift for a special someone don’t miss the Sudio Cyber week on until 28/11/23. Not only do they have great deals onsite but you can stack those deals and our 15% discount code ‘2AussieTravellers15’ for even more savings.

#sudio #sudioau #sudioaustralia

November to March is turtle nesting season on the Bundaberg coast. 

Mon Repos is the largest Loggerhead turtle rookery in the Southern Hemisphere and runs nightly tours through the season providing turtle education and giving the public the opportunity to see the female turtles come ashore to lay their eggs and later in summer the tiny hatchlings as they run down the beach to the ocean currents that will guide them through the early stage of their lives.

#visitbundaberg #southerngreatbarrierreef #monreposturtlecentre #seeaustralia #thisisqueensland
